<item>
 <title>Brass Transit</title>
 <link>http://jazz.to/artist/brass-transit</link>
 <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-web field-type-link-field field-label-inline clearfix field-wrapper&quot;&gt;&lt;div  class=&quot;field-label&quot;&gt;website:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.brasstransit.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;http://www.brasstransit.com/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-photo field-type-image field-label-hidden field-wrapper&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://jazz.to/sites/default/files/brass-transit-media-shot.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;body field&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Brass Transit - Toronto&#039;s dynamic, crowd-pleasing, studio-tight Chicago tribute!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The band&#039;s show includes all the hits from Chicago&#039;s golden age. With a world-class horn section, a rocking rhythm section and vocals stacked sky-high, Brass Transit transports its audience back to the freewheeling days of the seventies. The band includes veterans of the Hall-of-Fame rock and soul acts like the Drifters, Sam and Dave, Aretha Franklin, Ben E. King, the Marvelettes, Frankie Valli, Mary Wilson, Martha Reeves, Little Anthony &amp;amp; the Imperials, Del Shannon and the Mamas and the Papas.&lt;/p&gt;
